I think that was the funniest thing to happen to SV since Dwight Howard quoted Lex on the Office.
Who ever wrote that really did watch the show. Tee Heee
Jeez Smallville what a way to make me cry.  It has now officially hit me. Ten years and now its almost over. CAN NOT PROCESS THE EMOTIONS!
I want to be home so badly right now
I ma be far from home but YAYAYAYYAAY   Go Giants!!!!

Am I actually moving to Orlando, Florida?!  Checks itinerary...looks like it. 
Huh. Who knew.

Happy place. To me that was quite possibly awesome. Tom Welling rocked!

One day I hope to not sound like a 13yr old girl. One day. Obviously its not today cause....OMG

Does any one know the name of this story: 

The Kents die in the barn, possibly murdered. Clark having found them is hardly speaking. He walks around kinda numb.
Lex is the one to take him in. Lex helps Clark deal with some nightmares.
There's one scene where Pete ask why he isn't with him at the Ross house.

At the end Clark writes Lex a letter and Lex is frantic to find him which he does in a field.

Its bugging me that I can't find it.

I just want to make pie for a living people. 
Man I failed that interview...sigh

At WonderCon Geoff  was asked about if he would write more JSA for SV. Nothing Spoiler worthy. Just a quick 30sec clip.

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rTEu47ztvYk

Right after this and I kicked myself for pushing the stop recording button, the question was "How does it feel to be the sexiest man in the DC nation?"
 The crowd went crazy and cheered it up. Geoff blushed looked down, kind of like a Clark Kent AWW Shucks moment and said "wha..what's the next question?"  Adorable.

Went to WonderCon. Met Geoff Johns. Life = Good!

A five second video of him talking about SV to come. Nothing important just him liking the AJ episode.

I'm home alone.  Like always and watching the closing ceremonies.
Its humorous start and the celebration, the happy celebration with heart just got to me. 
I caught myself talking to the TV. Actually talking out loud about how cool that was O_o

Sitting here alone watching people party and be joyous at their achievements made me start bawling. 
People can do so much and I can't even figure how to plan a trip. ARGHH!
It feels so sad to me right now as I try to plan a trip for one. 
All the hotel rooms are automatically set for 2. And at this moment it hurts to click on the tab for just 1. 

And I just know I won't end up going anywhere at all.   I just don't know how to do any of this right.
I think i need to go for a run on the treadmill. I need to shake this sad stuff off somehow.

I'm just gonna sit here in this corner. 
The one over there.
 
Yup just sit and smile because I just threw the biggest squee! dance and am a little ashamed. Just a little, I'd gladly squee again and probably will once I finnish sitting in that corner.
That little corner over there.

Oh Smallville, am I your crack whore? Is this how you keep me tweaking for more?  Because that thing right there. The stuff you just gave me, so high about it right now.

This season like the eight have been as awesome as can be. Happy now.

Hee!

OK so that was my little comic lovin' heart going YES YES YES at the end there  The Ollie / speedy story kinda lost me. As in I really didn't care but the fact that  they wove the plot points together a bit really impressed me.  The morning show plot with Clark and Lois was cute. "I'm doing this for YOU!  " and " what about us lois is it love or war?"  Assertive Clark going for what he wants !  Super Clark catching that bullet like the bad ass he is! Blind Date Clark smooth and cool with a pretty girl! I love IT.

But my favorite of the night was Tess being fierce. That R.A.O company set up by Zod made me giggle cause the cool Kryptonian name asside its one of those OK SV well go with it for now. She is not one to mess with and  I believe Zod got the point. 

So thumbs up from me and bring up next week.

Shallow:
How are they all sooo pretty !!?? 
Applause to these actors parents. Well done

Show:
Thumbs up from me.
That's about it. I never claimed to be insightful.

Why is Neil Diamond singing to me on the CW when I should be watching a SV re-run?

I think my Friday night just got a little more pathetic with that sentence. WOW

To sister :  

Fuck you! Fuck the next outing that you want to do. Fuck every time that I helped you. You are the most ungrateful, pigheaded, greedy, egotistical, self-centered ASS I have come across. You’re an Ass.  Your husband is an ASS. Your good deeds are nothing but the façade that attempts to cover your Assy-ness.

 The world does not revolve around you and neither does my day, MY time nor MY patience. This is the Last time I put up with you. This is the Last time you take me for granted. Because I am done! Absolutely done with you and your way of treating me.  

Go live however you want to live and treat people.  But realize that no one on this earth is less than you. Stop treating people like they are puppets for you to play with.

So for my piece of mind I say FUCK YOU!

I’m going to enjoy my day.

 

*I wrote it down so I could recite it onto her voice mail. It felt so much better than crying alone.  *

Magic Mountain is full of Superheroes. Capes on Everyone!
For a $5 game you automatically get a DC Comic Superhero Cape. I picked Wonder Woman and OMG everyone in that park was wearing them. Little Supermen were walking with their Dad Flash. BatGirls were in line with me for the Superman ride. I took a picture with a Green Lantern!

Oh geez, Project Runway nice way to bring in the unnecessary drama. 

And for what? Those were just Ugly.

Geez, Tomb is just a really dark episode isn't it? And how much did Allison rock in this! I wonder why it was on my meh list and it took today viewing to get me so caught up in it.

Hey, I have the Kryptonite bracelet, but in blue. Well good going Urban Outfitters.

I saw Superman Returns and I liked it, but I'm completely bias cause I have a little crush on anything Superman. I went with my older brother, my sister, her boyfriend, and my 9 year old nephew. That's a big age range and we all had a blast watching it in IMAX 3-D. Some 3-D sequences didn't work for me but the cape was amazing. It was just so beautiful to see. 

I think it was the whole experience of getting together and everyone enjoying the day that made it so memorable. Plus they passed out Daly Plant newspapers while we we in line with little mock articles about the movie's plot points. It also has a great poster in it too. We all loved it. 


Random Question: Can you wash a regular pillow in a washing machine? One of my bed pillows got stuck under my bed one night and now has this mildew like smell. I kinda prefer it to smell like Downey, but that's just me.

Time to DANCE!!!

Anywhere, anyway, with music or with out, give a little shimmy. I won't look: do it naked. ::peek:: Get DOWN TONIGHT!

So I really don't watch Entourage but I think I might have to start.

I had a very, very real dream where Jeremy Piven and I were,... well getting to know each other with a lot of tongue, in very nice places I may add. 

:face palms: Too much? 

Now, no way was it a bad dream nor do I think The Piven is the bottom of the pretty latter but he's never crossed my mind before. It's always been the SV men or random guy in a baseball uniform. 

Oh my mind just went to a good place: Welling, Rosenbaum, dirty baseball uniforms, showers...dammit there goes Piven in there again. OUT! Out! I don't want another tv show to love.   

Dam HBO.

I don't know what it is about today but good god you guys are funny.  The minute I opened my flist I had read posts to giggle, laugh, and a couple of embarrassing snorts to explain.  Maybe its my good mood at becoming an aunt yesterday, or the beautiful spring days. (Wow I'm sounding hippy-ish right now aren't I?) I'm just happy and I usually don't feel Happy all the time. So, I want to share the Happy with everyone who LJ's there hearts out.

HAPPY!!!

http://www.i-am-bored.com/bored_link.cfm?link_id=8662


I'm scaring the mouse that I named charlie that squatting in my apartment...LAUGHING.

Office space meets the Justice League, or something like that. HAHAHAHAHAHAA.

God I hope I find this funny in the morning. IF not, I'm sorry.

*giggle*

I'm not the chick flick type of girl but the movie Ever After always makes me want to watch it over and over again. 

I need chocolate now. 

I started this journal to keep up on all my fannish love. But have I? Nooo. I guess the break of all my shows have something to do with it. Yeah, that's what I'm blaming it on.

And on that note: SV ROCKS!!!
I don't know what it is. At first I wanted everyone I know to watch it with me. Now it's something that I want to keep to myself. Like they won't get it anymore and make fun of my little obsession. It makes me happy watching it, as goofy as SV can get sometimes. But I'm in it for the long haul, Lexana and all. I can stand it because I go here and the Clex lives on. 

YOU GUYS ROCK!!!

Today i have watched Kinsey, Midnight in the Garden b/w Good and Evil, 2 Smallville eps, Hotel Rwanda, Stage Beauty and a random ep of Season 5 of Queer as Folk. 

Obviously productivity isn't my strongest quality, but dammit if I was going to stay on the couch to watch SV's Ageless. 

So I got up and made brownies. Soon I will eat brownies and after that I will be mad at myself that I ate to many brownies. 

This was a good lazy day.
